#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:4
msgid "begin - start a new block of code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:9
msgid "begin; [COMMANDS ...]; end"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:16
msgid "``begin`` is used to create a new block of code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:18
msgid ""
"A block allows the introduction of a new :ref:`variable scope <variables-"
"scope>`, redirection of the input or output of a set of commands as a group, "
"or to specify precedence when using the conditional commands like ``and``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:20
msgid ""
"The block is unconditionally executed. ``begin; ...; end`` is equivalent to "
"``if true; ...; end``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:22
msgid ""
"``begin`` does not change the current exit status itself. After the block "
"has completed, ``$status`` will be set to the status returned by the most "
"recent command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:24
msgid "The **-h** or **--help** option displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:27
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:29
msgid ""
"The following code sets a number of variables inside of a block scope. Since "
"the variables are set inside the block and have local scope, they will be "
"automatically deleted when the block ends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:33
msgid ""
"begin\n"
"    set -l PIRATE Yarrr\n"
"\n"
"    ...\n"
"end\n"
"\n"
"echo $PIRATE\n"
"# This will not output anything, since the PIRATE variable\n"
"# went out of scope at the end of the block"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:44
msgid "In the following code, all output is redirected to the file out.html."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/begin.rst:48
msgid ""
"begin\n"
"    echo $xml_header\n"
"    echo $html_header\n"
"    if test -e $file\n"
"        ...\n"
"    end\n"
"    ...\n"
"end > out.html"
msgstr ""
